## Context

- Report complete at reports/pandas_pans/pans-genetic-variant-pathway-analysis.md (committed c0a0145). No changes needed.
- Key findings: 37 enriched pathways (FDR<0.05). Lectin complement most significant (FDR=1.12e-05, MBL2/MASP1/MASP2). DDR/NER second cluster. TREX1-SAMHD1 cGAS-STING PPI module (score 0.921). mTOR convergence negative.
- Neuroinflammation cross-reference incomplete: GSE102482 GPL23038 uses transcript cluster IDs, needs annotation mapping.
- **Still deferred (MCP tools unavailable 7 consecutive runs):** update_project(findings_content, plain_summary, impact_score, novelty_summary, blind_spots) and task status updates. Content prepared:
  - plain_summary: "PANS is a condition where children suddenly develop OCD, tics, and anxiety after infections. This study analyzed the genes of 32 PANS patients and found their genetic variants cluster in two key immune pathways: the lectin complement system (which helps fight infections like strep) and a DNA-sensing pathway that controls inflammation. These findings suggest PANS patients may be genetically predisposed to abnormal immune responses to common infections."
  - impact_score: high
  - novelty_summary: "First systematic computational pathway analysis of PANS genetic variants. Identifies lectin complement (MBL2/MASP1/MASP2) as the most enriched pathway, directly linking genetic susceptibility to the known strep-triggered clinical presentation. Discovers a TREX1-SAMHD1 cGAS-STING module suggesting type I interferon dysregulation paralleling Aicardi-Goutieres syndrome."
  - blind_spots: "Small gene set (22 genes) and cohort (32 patients) limit statistical power. Neuroinflammation cross-reference with GSE102482 blocked by platform annotation issues. No functional validation of variant effects on pathway activity. VUS inclusion (5/22 genes) may introduce noise."
- No new tasks found. All writing work for this initiative is complete pending MCP availability.
